    <subfield code="y">00009 Detection of CDM--DE coupling, following an hypothetical determination of an electron neutrino mass $m_\nu \simeq 0.3~$eV, by the experiment KATRIN, yielding $M_\nu \simeq 0.9~$eV. Here we show the likelihood distribution, with such a prior on $M_\nu$. Colors andlines convey the same indications as in Figures 4 and 5.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="856" ind1="4" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="u">http://inspirehep.net/record/837240/files/bin2.png</subfield>
    <subfield code="y">00001 {\bf Left panel:} Transfer functions (multiplied by $k^{1.5}$, for graphic aims) in example cosmologies with/without coupling and with/without 2 massive $\nu$'s (00/CM models). {\bf Right panel:} Binned anisotropy spectral data, normalized to the best--fit $\Lambda$CDM model (upper frame) or to the best fit SUGRA cDE model including $\nu$--masses (lower frame). The distorsions arising whencoupling or $\nu$--mass are separately considered are also shown.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="856" ind1="4" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="u">http://inspirehep.net/record/837240/files/fig10.png</subfield>
    <subfield code="y">00008 Evolution of density parameters in a SUGRA model with coupling and $\nu$ mass. Colors refer to different components, as specified in the frame; lines to the different models: $M_\nu=0, ~\beta=0$ (continuous line); $M_\nu=0.5~$eV, $\beta = 0.085$ (dotted); $M_\nu=1.1~$eV, $\beta = 0.17$ (short dashed); $M_\nu=1.2~$eV, $\beta= 0.22$ (long dashed).</subfield>
  </datafield>
