    <subfield code="y">00002 Marginalized (solid line) and average (dotted line) likelihood of cosmological parameters in SUGRA models. Notice that the $\beta$ signal appears when high-- and low--$z$ data are put together, and is strengthened by SNIa data. As a matter of fact, coupling allows to lower the ``tension'' between $\Omega_c$ and fluctuation amplitude detected from CMB and deep sample data. For $M_{\nu}$ we also show the corresponding likelihood distributions obtained in the case of a standard $\Lambda$CDM+$M_\nu$ model (graylines).</subfield>
